[SNOWMOBILE ENGINE RUMBLING]

02:57.046 --> 02:58.915
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

03:33.448 --> 03:34.350
[GRUNTS]

03:40.456 --> 03:41.858
[GROANS]

03:59.908 --> 04:02.410
Ah!

04:02.412 --> 04:03.313
[GROANS]

04:11.388 --> 04:13.289
[GRUNTING]

04:28.339 --> 04:29.741
[YELLING]

05:08.279 --> 05:09.180
[SIGHS]

05:49.687 --> 05:51.590
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

06:42.075 --> 06:43.976
[TAPPING]

06:59.559 --> 07:00.960
[WATER POURING]

07:38.966 --> 07:40.368
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

07:45.206 --> 07:45.707
Sleep.

08:20.707 --> 08:22.109
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

09:44.060 --> 09:45.963
[STEAM HISSING]

09:49.031 --> 09:51.435
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

10:11.488 --> 10:13.391
[STEAM HISSING]

10:24.468 --> 10:26.371
[STEAM HISSING]

10:32.475 --> 10:33.541
Hey.

10:33.543 --> 10:34.845
DISPATCHER [OVER RADIO]:
All units respond.

10:43.454 --> 10:44.822
[SIREN WAILING]

11:05.409 --> 11:07.278
[CHATTER OVER PA SYSTEM]

12:32.232 --> 12:35.102
PRIEST: [SPEAKING LATIN]

12:45.212 --> 12:47.379
This is all he had on him.

12:47.381 --> 12:48.980
DAVIES: And has it been
returned to the family?

12:48.982 --> 12:51.115
KAPPA: Well, not yet.

12:51.117 --> 12:52.616
DAVIES: Anything else?

12:52.618 --> 12:54.619
KAPPA: Yeah, the slugs were
made from a frozen polymer.

12:54.621 --> 12:57.788
It melts just after impact,
so you can forget ballistics.

12:57.790 --> 13:01.225
The scene of the crime was wet
and steamy, so no fingerprints.

13:01.227 --> 13:02.360
Then, obviously, a rookie.

13:02.362 --> 13:03.961
Yeah, no shit.

13:03.963 --> 13:05.696
Katy buy you a new suit?

13:05.698 --> 13:07.465
Discount days at Macy's.

13:07.467 --> 13:08.366
Yeah, that's nice.

13:08.368 --> 13:10.601
The blue was an option.

13:10.603 --> 13:13.606
Fuck you.

13:13.608 --> 13:15.006
According to the
manual, the killer

13:15.008 --> 13:16.508
should be present at
the victim's funeral.

13:16.510 --> 13:17.543
According to the manual...

13:17.545 --> 13:18.878
you've been watching
too much Netflix.

13:18.880 --> 13:20.245
DAVIES: I love "True Detective."

13:20.247 --> 13:21.847
Ah, forget it.

13:21.849 --> 13:22.648
Nothing happens here.

13:22.650 --> 13:25.418
We're too close to Canada.

13:25.420 --> 13:26.852
They have that in New York?

13:26.854 --> 13:27.754
What's that, funerals?

13:27.756 --> 13:29.621
Netflix.

13:29.623 --> 13:30.789
Oh, believe me, man.

13:30.791 --> 13:32.493
New York homicide, you
don't need Netflix.

13:35.363 --> 13:38.832
So tell me, how come a guy
who's worth $200 million

13:38.834 --> 13:40.533
comes to live in a lost
fucking town like this?

13:40.535 --> 13:42.134
He was born here.

13:42.136 --> 13:45.837
In this town, everything
belongs to him.

13:45.839 --> 13:47.872
Well, we followed the manual...

13:47.874 --> 13:51.143
came to see if the killer
turned up to the funeral.

13:51.145 --> 13:52.410
He didn't know the manual.

13:52.412 --> 13:53.712
Oh, he didn't know the manual.
Got it.

13:53.714 --> 13:54.813
That's why he
didn't come here.

13:54.815 --> 13:56.383
OK.
Come on.

14:04.593 --> 14:08.127
Mr. Brigleur.

14:08.129 --> 14:08.630
Brigleur.

14:12.468 --> 14:15.101
I know this may sound
like a stupid question,

14:15.103 --> 14:18.505
but did Mr. Kessler
have a lot of enemies?

14:18.507 --> 14:21.406
An industrialist of his
stature only has enemies.

14:21.408 --> 14:24.111
It's a mark of importance.

14:24.113 --> 14:26.246
You hear that, Davies?

14:26.248 --> 14:27.646
He must be very important.

14:27.648 --> 14:28.517
No shit, right?

14:31.552 --> 14:33.987
Huh?

14:33.989 --> 14:35.458
You haven't asked
me any more question.

14:38.660 --> 14:41.694
So you're the executor
of Mr. Kessler's

14:41.696 --> 14:45.131
last will and testament
as well as his properties.

14:45.133 --> 14:47.602
I already know that.

14:47.604 --> 14:53.108
What do you know, that
you're the number-one suspect?

14:53.110 --> 14:55.343
What?
Are you not going to answer?

14:55.345 --> 14:55.913
Nothing to say?

14:58.615 --> 15:00.981
That was not a question
but a supposition

15:00.983 --> 15:02.617
with an affirmative tone.

15:02.619 --> 15:06.020
OK, well, consider
it a question.

15:06.022 --> 15:11.161
Mr. Kessler has a descendant
by the name of Charlie Kessler.

15:16.999 --> 15:19.566
If the heir should
die, the Kessler Group

15:19.568 --> 15:23.470
would be broken up, its
division sold off separately,

15:23.472 --> 15:28.709
exactly which most of their
opponents had been hoping for.

15:28.711 --> 15:31.011
So you lose your job, right?

15:31.013 --> 15:36.785
Therefore, I have no interest
in the disappearance of Iver.

15:36.787 --> 15:40.689
Do I remain at the top
of your list of suspects?

15:40.691 --> 15:42.423
Just the one wife?

15:42.425 --> 15:46.796
Just one, confined to a
mental home over 10 years ago.

15:46.798 --> 15:49.697
She has lost all memory and
is, therefore, incapable

15:49.699 --> 15:53.268
ever suffering any
sense of loss, so...

15:53.270 --> 15:54.402
OK.

15:54.404 --> 15:59.307
So if I wanted to meet
this Charlie Kessler?

15:59.309 --> 16:00.310
His address is secret.

16:03.847 --> 16:08.148
Inside, you will find the
proof that Charlie was in Paris

16:08.150 --> 16:09.984
at the time of the murder.

16:09.986 --> 16:10.685
[LIGHTS CLICKING OFF]

16:10.687 --> 16:11.353
[ELECTRIC CRACKLING]

16:11.355 --> 16:12.153
Shit.

16:12.155 --> 16:12.954
Second time today.

16:12.956 --> 16:14.156
Hey, I'm sorry.

16:14.158 --> 16:15.724
It happens a lot.

16:15.726 --> 16:17.158
May I leave now?

16:17.160 --> 16:19.561
Yeah, sure.

16:19.563 --> 16:21.129
Oh, I'll show you out.

16:21.131 --> 16:22.196
No need.

16:22.198 --> 16:24.134
Got a good memory,
and I know your office

16:24.136 --> 16:26.105
only has a single corridor.

17:26.397 --> 17:28.801
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

18:11.011 --> 18:12.309
REPORTER [ON RADIO]:
Fighting broke out

18:12.311 --> 18:14.078
overnight between
rival factions along

18:14.080 --> 18:15.813
the Israeli-Syrian border.

18:15.815 --> 18:17.415
The initial reports
claim Israeli...

18:17.417 --> 18:18.383
I need to go here.

18:18.385 --> 18:19.651
REPORTER [ON RADIO]:
...jet fighters

18:19.653 --> 18:20.652
bombed a guerrilla base,
killing at least 40 soldiers...

18:20.654 --> 18:21.720
That's far.

18:21.722 --> 18:23.253
REPORTER [ON RADIO]:
...and 13 civilians.

18:23.255 --> 18:25.056
Damage to the base
is said to be heavy,

18:25.058 --> 18:26.557
and the Israeli
jets are reported

18:26.559 --> 18:27.293
to have made it back to...

18:30.330 --> 18:32.198
[PHONE RINGING]

18:42.109 --> 18:43.674
MAN [ON PHONE]: Can we talk?

18:43.676 --> 18:45.646
This is not a secure line.

19:24.985 --> 19:27.389
[REGGAE MUSIC ON RADIO]

19:39.333 --> 19:41.967
You the snowmobile rental man?

19:41.969 --> 19:44.803
Where you going?

19:44.805 --> 19:45.906
To the Pacific.

19:45.908 --> 19:47.109
[LAUGHS]

19:48.110 --> 19:50.476
I'm not a travel agency.

19:50.478 --> 19:52.146
So?

19:52.148 --> 19:52.913
Trust me.

19:52.915 --> 19:54.183
A plane is less risky.

19:59.854 --> 20:00.589
Planes scare me.

20:04.459 --> 20:06.859
Hey, uh, there's
no daily special?

20:06.861 --> 20:08.727
A daily special?

20:08.729 --> 20:10.430
- No.
- OK.

20:10.432 --> 20:13.565
All right, I'll do the
cheese and no pickles.

20:13.567 --> 20:14.400
Never been any.

20:14.402 --> 20:17.436
Oh, good.

20:17.438 --> 20:18.472
A Bud?

20:18.474 --> 20:19.705
Oh, you got something else?

20:19.707 --> 20:20.907
Some tea, maybe?

20:20.909 --> 20:21.974
Coffee.

20:21.976 --> 20:24.111
Same as this?

20:24.113 --> 20:24.879
Yes.

20:24.881 --> 20:26.179
Oh, a Bud then.

20:26.181 --> 20:28.549
Thanks.

20:28.551 --> 20:30.150
This place is the
back end of nowhere.

20:30.152 --> 20:30.918
Yeah, no shit.

20:30.920 --> 20:32.552
They got Bud.

20:32.554 --> 20:33.888
What the hell
are we doing here?

20:33.890 --> 20:36.658
Well, they found an old sea
plane about five years ago,

20:36.660 --> 20:37.491
crashed.

20:37.493 --> 20:38.927
Maybe the pilot is on the side.

20:38.929 --> 20:40.460
I don't fucking know.

20:40.462 --> 20:41.695
[INAUDIBLE] a little bit.

20:41.697 --> 20:42.933
Yeah, no worse
than this coffee.

20:48.036 --> 20:49.570
That was quick.

20:49.572 --> 20:50.772
Microwave.

20:50.774 --> 20:53.440
Oh, great.

20:53.442 --> 20:55.042
They have a saying
here that says,

20:55.044 --> 20:56.777
once you learn how
to walk, they're

20:56.779 --> 20:57.777
going to have to shoot you.

20:57.779 --> 20:59.312
That's nice.

20:59.314 --> 21:02.616
I was already fascinated
that a guy from New York

21:02.618 --> 21:05.419
asked to be transferred here.

21:05.421 --> 21:08.322
Been a long time since
anyone fascinated me, buddy.

21:08.324 --> 21:12.026
Oh, Kiki told me, if I
leave you alone too long,

21:12.028 --> 21:13.361
you're going to get lost.

21:13.363 --> 21:16.234
Yeah, well, maybe
I want to get lost.

22:04.482 --> 22:05.881
Are you OK?

22:05.883 --> 22:07.216
Yeah, I'm OK.

22:07.218 --> 22:09.718
There's no problem.

22:09.720 --> 22:12.522
There's nothing for 60 miles.

22:12.524 --> 22:13.025
I know.

22:16.228 --> 22:18.596
I manage an inn an hour
away from here if you want.

22:25.670 --> 22:26.572
You're welcome.

24:12.945 --> 24:14.347
[SNOWMOBILE WHINING]

24:16.950 --> 24:17.950
[WOMAN YELLS]

24:17.952 --> 24:18.950
[CRASHING]

24:18.952 --> 24:20.354
[CROWS CAWING]

24:25.425 --> 24:27.329
[METALLIC TAPPING]

24:48.883 --> 24:50.785
[DOOR SQUEAKING]

25:34.295 --> 25:36.698
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

25:48.776 --> 25:49.678
[GASPS]

25:56.185 --> 25:58.653
There are five more
that needs to be removed.

25:58.655 --> 26:00.023
[MOANS]

26:01.090 --> 26:01.789
Ah!

26:01.791 --> 26:03.023
No, no.

26:03.025 --> 26:07.627
The more you tense your
muscles, the more it will hurt.

26:07.629 --> 26:09.597
No, no, no.

26:09.599 --> 26:13.470
Ah, ah, ah!
Fuck.

26:22.478 --> 26:26.915
[SINGING] Since I fear
you'll leave me behind

26:26.917 --> 26:35.356
on the [INAUDIBLE]
Learning [INAUDIBLE],,

26:35.358 --> 26:38.962
learning your smile
when you come my way.

26:41.831 --> 26:44.531
You know, it's pretty
cool you can smoke here.

26:44.533 --> 26:46.600
Oh, here you have a choice.

26:46.602 --> 26:48.837
You do your dying
to colds or cancer.

26:48.839 --> 26:50.571
Hm.

26:50.573 --> 26:52.407
This place is like
a time machine, man.

26:52.409 --> 26:54.076
You sure this is legal?

26:54.078 --> 26:55.910
You see any other officers?

26:55.912 --> 26:56.945
Good point.

26:56.947 --> 26:57.878
DAVIES: Thanks, Mary.

26:57.880 --> 26:59.080
Ice cream, really?

26:59.082 --> 27:00.415
I can't get enough.

27:00.417 --> 27:02.818
Well, I suppose it
reduces the risk of thermal

27:02.820 --> 27:03.852
shock when the [INAUDIBLE].

27:03.854 --> 27:04.921
[LAUGHTER]

27:06.690 --> 27:07.656
You don't mind, right?

27:07.658 --> 27:08.659
I'm going to go pay.

27:12.530 --> 27:17.965
[SINGING] Looking for
once a better time to love.

27:17.967 --> 27:20.569
Forget her.

27:20.571 --> 27:24.706
It'll be good for you to
move on to something else.

27:24.708 --> 27:28.077
I think that's what
God said to Jesus, right?

27:28.079 --> 27:32.781
What are you waiting
for, her coming back?

27:32.783 --> 27:38.420
I'm not waiting for
anything, not anymore.

27:38.422 --> 27:39.821
Hey, guys, listen.

27:39.823 --> 27:41.690
The music's pretty good tonight,
so I'm going to stick around.

27:41.692 --> 27:43.859
And it was lovely to see you.

27:43.861 --> 27:45.227
Well, take care.

27:45.229 --> 27:46.129
Thanks for dinner.

27:46.131 --> 27:48.665
No problem.

27:48.667 --> 27:49.599
Did you tell him?

27:49.601 --> 27:50.966
Not tonight, honey.

27:50.968 --> 27:52.802
The more you wait, the
harder it's gonna get.

27:52.804 --> 27:53.969
Oh, I know.

27:53.971 --> 27:55.437
I know,

27:55.439 --> 27:57.342
[WIND HOWLING]

28:18.362 --> 28:19.264
[GROANS]

28:20.364 --> 28:22.765
I can't leave it outside.

28:22.767 --> 28:27.504
Before sunrise, the wolves
would strip it to the bone.

28:27.506 --> 28:30.440
Food is rare this time of year.

28:30.442 --> 28:33.677
You'll need plenty of protein.

28:33.679 --> 28:39.783
If you don't relax,
your bones won't heal.

28:39.785 --> 28:43.919
And in six weeks, there'll
be no more ice on the roads.

28:43.921 --> 28:46.489
You'll need a boat.

28:46.491 --> 28:47.326
Have a good night.

28:53.865 --> 28:55.733
Hey, you received this.

28:55.735 --> 28:56.499
Yeah, what is it?

28:56.501 --> 28:59.335
It's from Kessler.

28:59.337 --> 29:03.274
It's the ballistic report
you requested at the time.

29:03.276 --> 29:04.408
And what did it say?

29:04.410 --> 29:07.879
It's about the ice bullet.

29:07.881 --> 29:10.748
They say not many people
can use that, such a weapon.

29:10.750 --> 29:11.951
It includes a list too.

29:47.354 --> 29:47.854
MELODY: Thank you.

29:52.425 --> 29:55.028
Um, my name is Melody.

30:01.602 --> 30:04.036
And I don't know
what I would have

30:04.038 --> 30:05.269
done if you hadn't found me.

30:05.271 --> 30:06.407
What are you doing here?

30:09.743 --> 30:11.879
I had an accident
on my snowmobile.

30:16.282 --> 30:19.251
I followed the slope
when I saw smoke.

30:19.253 --> 30:21.689
What were you doing on
the snowmobile around here?

30:26.426 --> 30:29.128
I'm crossing the Rockies.

30:29.130 --> 30:31.662
I've been planning
to do it for a year.

30:31.664 --> 30:33.699
HIT MAN: All by yourself?

30:33.701 --> 30:36.438
I live all year in buildings,
and this is a real luxury.

30:40.374 --> 30:45.710
I purposely came here not
to be bothered by people.

30:45.712 --> 30:48.547
I... well, I'm sorry.

30:48.549 --> 30:51.884
And I'll leave as soon as I can.

30:51.886 --> 30:52.751
How?

30:52.753 --> 30:55.389
I don't know, uh...

30:55.391 --> 30:56.989
by road?

30:56.991 --> 31:00.360
There are no roads
here, only the frozen ice

31:00.362 --> 31:01.397
that forms in winter.

31:04.165 --> 31:06.365
Give me a good
reason to help you,

31:06.367 --> 31:08.201
or you leave tomorrow
by foot, and they

31:08.203 --> 31:11.072
fish you out with the
salmon when the snow melts.

31:14.809 --> 31:15.310
Melody.

31:27.254 --> 31:28.889
Your clothes are clean and dry.

31:28.891 --> 31:29.725
You should put them on.

31:33.528 --> 31:35.762
[INAUDIBLE] some time
to look at the list.

31:35.764 --> 31:37.397
Two names don't
make a list, Captain.

31:37.399 --> 31:40.267
The first person has been
locked up for five years.

31:40.269 --> 31:41.134
OK.

31:41.136 --> 31:42.336
I looked him up.

31:42.338 --> 31:45.272
The second is a sniper
for elite special forces.

31:45.274 --> 31:47.641
That's pretty hot shit.

31:47.643 --> 31:50.377
Tropical, even, especially
after he was in Iraq

31:50.379 --> 31:51.512
during the time of the murder.

31:51.514 --> 31:53.748
Yeah, well, Iraq's the
Middle East, Captain.

31:53.750 --> 31:54.781
It's not the tropics.

31:54.783 --> 31:55.782
Who gives a damn?

31:55.784 --> 31:56.851
He's not our man.

31:56.853 --> 31:58.819
Hey, we still need
to find the address

31:58.821 --> 31:59.988
of the guy who made him, OK?

31:59.990 --> 32:01.588
Those two names are just
the tip of the iceberg.

32:01.590 --> 32:02.823
It's been 10 months.

32:02.825 --> 32:03.758
You're wasting your time.

32:03.760 --> 32:05.625
You got something else to do?

32:05.627 --> 32:06.361
Yeah, right.

32:06.363 --> 32:07.393
Who cares?

32:07.395 --> 32:08.796
- What did Kessler do to you?
- Nothing.

32:08.798 --> 32:10.163
I just like to finish
what I started.

32:10.165 --> 32:11.298
You know what I mean.

32:11.300 --> 32:13.768
Hey, Bob, can you
check these names?

32:13.770 --> 32:15.502
They made calls
during the funeral.

32:15.504 --> 32:16.970
Check them against
Brigleur's contact list.

32:16.972 --> 32:18.838
See if any of them match, OK?

32:18.840 --> 32:20.142
[PHONE RINGING]

32:21.610 --> 32:22.577
Check them all?

32:22.579 --> 32:23.246
Yeah, check them all.

32:26.550 --> 32:30.219
Hey, why the face?

32:30.221 --> 32:31.155
I received my transfer.

32:34.457 --> 32:37.525
Well, congratulations.

32:37.527 --> 32:40.128
You received notice
for my transfer...

32:40.130 --> 32:41.429
Uh, yeah.

32:41.431 --> 32:42.931
...three weeks ago, and you
didn't bother opening it.

32:42.933 --> 32:45.667
Sorry.
It's an old habit of mine.

32:45.669 --> 32:48.002
Oh, I already
knew a month, but I

32:48.004 --> 32:48.939
couldn't just face telling you.

32:52.309 --> 32:56.110
I put in a request
for my replacement.

32:56.112 --> 32:57.378
You're going to get promoted.

32:57.380 --> 32:58.814
[CHUCKLES]

32:58.816 --> 33:00.081
You'll need to
fill out some papers.

33:00.083 --> 33:01.217
Shit.

33:01.219 --> 33:03.885
And I'm going to have
to call you Sheriff now.

33:03.887 --> 33:04.752
Go fuck yourself.

33:04.754 --> 33:07.022
I'm not the sheriff.

33:07.024 --> 33:12.095
Listen, I just don't
know how to say goodbye.

33:12.097 --> 33:14.633
It's easy.
Goodbye.

33:18.102 --> 33:18.603
Goodbye.

33:22.674 --> 33:25.043
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

33:38.022 --> 33:39.425
[GASPING]

33:49.466 --> 33:51.701
How long was I sleeping?

33:51.703 --> 33:53.703
Enough.

33:53.705 --> 33:55.040
You must start
training tomorrow.

33:58.010 --> 33:59.342
What training?

33:59.344 --> 34:02.913
You'll have to
walk far and quickly.

34:02.915 --> 34:05.816
Well, what about
my snowmobile?

34:05.818 --> 34:06.319
I don't know.

34:09.889 --> 34:12.422
I'll bring it back if I can.

34:12.425 --> 34:14.422
I haven't done
anything to you.

34:14.425 --> 34:19.463
I found you, fed
you, cared for you.

34:19.465 --> 34:22.130
It is up to you to do
what is necessary to leave

34:22.132 --> 34:25.135
this house as soon as possible.

34:25.137 --> 34:28.103
Am I making myself clear?

34:28.106 --> 34:28.873
Crystal clear.

34:32.311 --> 34:34.512
There is water
are on the table.

34:34.514 --> 34:36.349
If you want a drink, you
will have to stand up.

34:46.926 --> 34:49.295
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

35:34.208 --> 35:35.209
Ah!
Fuck.

35:41.816 --> 35:43.218
[GROANING]

36:47.683 --> 36:49.585
[SNOWMOBILE WHIRRING]

36:53.654 --> 36:55.557
[WATER DRIPPING]

37:02.131 --> 37:03.531
[MOANS]

37:13.110 --> 37:14.510
[GROWLING]

37:20.115 --> 37:22.518
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

37:29.592 --> 37:30.994
[WOLF HOWLS]

37:51.880 --> 37:52.982
What caused the accident?

37:57.955 --> 38:00.522
If an animal had
crossed your path,

38:00.524 --> 38:02.658
there would have been traces.

38:02.660 --> 38:04.792
Why?

38:04.794 --> 38:07.830
I don't know.

38:07.832 --> 38:09.167
[PANTING]

38:10.667 --> 38:13.134
Maybe I just fell asleep.

38:13.136 --> 38:15.236
In this cold?

38:15.238 --> 38:18.573
I... I lost control.

38:18.575 --> 38:19.910
[SIGHS]

38:27.718 --> 38:28.586
[GASPS]

38:30.620 --> 38:32.654
I need to understand.

38:32.656 --> 38:35.723
There's nothing to understand.

38:35.725 --> 38:37.692
Is it so important?

38:37.694 --> 38:38.196
Yes.

38:43.866 --> 38:47.235
I had a stand-off
with a wolf earlier,

38:47.237 --> 38:50.539
and he has tasted human blood...

38:50.541 --> 38:53.141
yours.

38:53.143 --> 38:55.478
Is that serious?

38:55.480 --> 38:58.313
A wolf never forget
the taste of blood.

38:58.315 --> 39:00.382
It won't give up
searching for it.

39:00.384 --> 39:04.288
Sooner or later, I'll
have to kill him.

39:13.630 --> 39:14.798
Hey, Sheriff.

39:14.800 --> 39:17.800
I found two matching
numbers on the list.

39:17.802 --> 39:20.269
Thanks.

39:20.271 --> 39:22.572
Good night, Sheriff.

39:22.574 --> 39:24.643
Sheriff... sheriff, my ass.

39:47.934 --> 39:49.569
Brigleur didn't want to
talk to you, Malcolm?

40:34.581 --> 40:35.649
Here is your bag.

41:18.158 --> 41:20.325
What are you doing?

41:20.327 --> 41:22.794
You still have a piece
of wood under the skin.

41:22.796 --> 41:28.466
If I don't remove it, you
won't stand no chance.

41:28.468 --> 41:29.434
Drink.

41:29.436 --> 41:30.803
It's going to be painful.

41:30.805 --> 41:32.007
It already is.

41:42.483 --> 41:42.984
Bite.

41:52.526 --> 41:54.428
[SCREAMS]

41:56.030 --> 41:57.431
[SCREAMS]

42:25.895 --> 42:27.295
[REGGAE MUSIC ON RADIO]

42:29.297 --> 42:29.799
Hi, there.

42:32.967 --> 42:37.503
Um, I'm looking for her.

42:37.505 --> 42:38.274
Are you the police?

42:42.344 --> 42:46.247
Does it make a difference?

42:46.249 --> 42:48.149
[INAUDIBLE]

42:48.151 --> 42:51.251
Did she leave an
address, a destination?

42:51.253 --> 42:56.457
[LAUGHS] Yeah, Pacific Ocean.

42:56.459 --> 42:59.626
And just in case something
went wrong, is there

42:59.628 --> 43:01.662
a way to find her or what?

43:01.664 --> 43:03.497
There is a satellite
beep under the seat

43:03.499 --> 43:07.635
in case of emergency,
but it must be activated.

43:07.637 --> 43:10.338
Otherwise, it
drains the battery.

43:10.340 --> 43:14.642
I need a snowmobile
and cans of gasoline.

43:14.644 --> 43:16.209
Sure.

43:16.211 --> 43:18.546
What name do I put on the bill?

43:18.548 --> 43:22.483
There are no bills,
much less a name.

43:22.485 --> 43:26.486
But if that beeper
emits anything,

43:26.488 --> 43:28.758
send a message to this
number immediately.

44:02.859 --> 44:04.558
Am I dying?

44:04.560 --> 44:06.627
You could have.

44:06.629 --> 44:07.397
But you're fine now.

44:12.169 --> 44:12.904
You should eat now.

44:19.210 --> 44:19.711
Thank you.

44:22.847 --> 44:24.650
I'm not used to saving people.

44:47.838 --> 44:49.574
I've [INAUDIBLE] the
stuff that was inside.

44:54.478 --> 44:56.378
There are no cell
phone in your bag.

44:56.380 --> 44:59.914
You don't want anyone
to find you, do you?

44:59.916 --> 45:00.883
No.

45:00.885 --> 45:02.418
It's just a week
away from my phone.

45:02.420 --> 45:02.988
That's the deal.

45:08.392 --> 45:09.193
My name is Henry.

45:59.279 --> 46:00.514
Here you are.

46:03.382 --> 46:06.885
Yeah, I took your advice.

46:06.887 --> 46:10.287
You've changed your clothes.

46:10.289 --> 46:14.191
What, do you have eyes
in the back of your head?

46:14.193 --> 46:15.329
I sense washing powder.

46:19.099 --> 46:20.898
You can smell that from there?

46:20.900 --> 46:24.101
I enjoy the same smells
every minute of the day here.

46:24.103 --> 46:26.072
Anything new gets
noted very quickly.

46:30.811 --> 46:34.144
I don't know how
you stand it out here.

46:34.146 --> 46:36.246
You mean like in the cities?

46:36.248 --> 46:39.483
Yeah, but there's
nothing here.

46:39.485 --> 46:45.190
Well, if nothing means no
noise, no pollution, no cars,

46:45.192 --> 46:48.593
no Starbucks, then,
yes, there is nothing

46:48.595 --> 46:52.230
here, at least nothing useless.

46:52.232 --> 46:55.002
But if you look closely, you'll
find everything you need.

47:12.153 --> 47:17.522
In a couple of days' time, we
will be walking for long hours.

47:17.524 --> 47:19.859
We?

47:19.861 --> 47:23.995
HENRY: Or I'll just drop you
off where there is no danger.

47:23.997 --> 47:26.631
What danger?

47:26.633 --> 47:27.635
Where you can survive.

47:33.308 --> 47:35.742
Is that why you were so
mad when I first got here?

47:35.744 --> 47:36.245
Partly.

47:39.748 --> 47:40.715
"The Art of War?"

47:43.951 --> 47:47.186
Did your wife take the rest of
the books when she left you?

47:47.188 --> 47:49.722
I had no other books...

47:49.724 --> 47:52.793
nor wife, for the matter.

47:52.795 --> 47:53.594
Sorry.

47:53.596 --> 47:56.096
I can be nosy at times.

47:56.098 --> 47:56.799
HENRY: At times?

48:03.137 --> 48:05.137
Such a man's book.

48:05.139 --> 48:08.474
The ultimate aim
of war is not to win

48:08.476 --> 48:12.744
costly victories but to
prepare long-lasting peace.

48:12.746 --> 48:15.047
Sun Tzu was a philosopher.

48:15.049 --> 48:17.218
Um, war is not an art.

48:43.646 --> 48:45.047
[LAUGHS]

48:50.153 --> 48:51.952
You want to know
something funny?

48:51.954 --> 48:53.421
Nope.

48:53.423 --> 48:54.388
Right.

48:54.390 --> 48:56.689
You don't laugh.

48:56.691 --> 48:58.325
Rarely when cutting logs.

48:58.327 --> 48:59.562
[SNICKERS]

49:01.463 --> 49:04.531
What's so funny?

49:04.533 --> 49:06.466
I was just asking
myself, is it

49:06.468 --> 49:09.603
necessary for a mountaineer
to be so serious

49:09.605 --> 49:12.306
when he chops wood?

49:12.308 --> 49:17.080
I'm not a mountaineer,
but I have adapted.

49:20.951 --> 49:22.951
Here.

49:22.953 --> 49:23.688
Don't move.

49:27.424 --> 49:28.290
What is this?

49:28.292 --> 49:30.592
Hold still.

49:30.594 --> 49:35.898
The plant containing the most
silica, perfect for fractures.

49:35.900 --> 49:40.369
It strengthen both the
bones and the cartilage.

49:40.371 --> 49:44.072
Well, why didn't
you use it sooner?

49:44.074 --> 49:48.409
Because putting a splint
or a cast on a hematoma,

49:48.411 --> 49:50.512
it is useless.

49:50.514 --> 49:53.648
It would be like if I
was trying to chalk you.

49:53.650 --> 49:55.083
Oh, yeah?

49:55.085 --> 49:57.318
You were never tempted?

49:57.320 --> 50:00.823
Now you can use your arm.

50:00.825 --> 50:02.861
Ribs are just a matter of time.

50:08.066 --> 50:10.365
Well, for someone who's
not used to saving people,

50:10.367 --> 50:12.401
you seem to know
what you're doing.

50:12.403 --> 50:15.138
I've been through a lot.

50:15.140 --> 50:19.975
I do my best not to be
dependent upon anybody.

50:19.977 --> 50:23.613
And you say that
for my benefit.

50:23.615 --> 50:25.950
You still haven't told me
what you were doing here.

50:35.760 --> 50:37.662
[WIND HOWLING]

50:38.796 --> 50:40.263
COMMENTATOR [ON TV]:
[INAUDIBLE] shot,

50:40.265 --> 50:41.765
high and just missed it in.

50:41.767 --> 50:44.767
Pulls back out on the
[INAUDIBLE] the puck.

50:44.769 --> 50:45.638
Penalty is over...

50:50.243 --> 50:51.643
[CHATTER]

51:04.757 --> 51:06.123
I guess you want a coffee?

51:06.125 --> 51:08.324
Yeah.

51:08.326 --> 51:10.127
You have any vacancies?

51:10.129 --> 51:14.197
Well, we won't put you
out in this time of night.

51:14.199 --> 51:16.366
It's going to hit tonight.

51:16.368 --> 51:17.634
Hit?

51:17.636 --> 51:19.605
Well, here, the
cold, it hurts.

51:25.143 --> 51:27.546
[SOFT PIANO PLAYING]

51:40.025 --> 51:42.492
ANNOUNCER 1 [ON TV]: And in the
end zone [INAUDIBLE] the play.

51:42.494 --> 51:49.401
[INAUDIBLE] field has been
[INAUDIBLE] in the end zone,

51:49.403 --> 51:50.804
and that's a touchdown.

51:58.211 --> 52:00.311
Down.
It's intercepted.

52:00.313 --> 52:01.780
It's picked off.

52:01.782 --> 52:03.881
ANNOUNCER 2 [ON TV]: Yeah,
and this one is underway.

52:03.883 --> 52:08.653
And the kick into the end zone,
being run out for 4 yards.

52:08.655 --> 52:11.122
And Cooper still
on his feet gets

52:11.124 --> 52:13.090
extra yards down the sideline.

52:13.092 --> 52:15.461
Ferrell trying to
out-race the Jaguars...

52:42.290 --> 52:46.457
Captain, how's life?

52:46.459 --> 52:49.194
Oh, you know, not too much
going on for me these days,

52:49.196 --> 52:50.429
just trying to keep busy.

52:50.431 --> 52:54.500
I'm about to give Kessler's
watch back to his wife.

52:54.502 --> 52:55.634
Look, I'm heading in right now.

52:55.636 --> 52:57.136
I'll call you later, OK?

52:57.138 --> 52:59.504
All right, bye.
Hi.

52:59.506 --> 53:01.172
Hi.

53:01.174 --> 53:02.141
Nice place.

53:02.143 --> 53:03.345
- Follow me.
- Nice.

53:06.180 --> 53:07.946
Not more than 15 minutes.

53:07.948 --> 53:09.048
OK.

53:09.050 --> 53:10.349
No contact.

53:10.351 --> 53:10.983
Yeah.

53:10.985 --> 53:13.519
She could panic.

53:13.521 --> 53:17.824
Speak slowly, and do
not contradict her.

53:17.826 --> 53:18.825
Understood?

53:18.827 --> 53:19.395
Yeah, yeah.

53:24.499 --> 53:25.001
Thank you.

53:28.436 --> 53:30.804
Hi.

53:30.806 --> 53:32.206
You don't know me.
But, um...

53:32.208 --> 53:35.575
It's a long time
since I've known anyone.

53:35.577 --> 53:37.313
- Please.
- Thank you.

53:40.048 --> 53:41.447
Look, I, uh...

53:41.449 --> 53:44.083
I don't want to stir up any
painful memories for you.

53:44.085 --> 53:48.856
In my state, a memory could
be miraculous and never painful.

53:48.858 --> 53:52.226
And you don't find it
unsettling, the forgetting?

53:52.228 --> 53:56.997
Young man, that question
is as naive as a description.

53:56.999 --> 54:00.268
How can we know what
we've already forgotten?

54:00.270 --> 54:05.272
My only fear is losing
what I still know.

54:05.274 --> 54:10.410
I cling to it each and
every day, like a lifeline.

54:10.412 --> 54:18.819
But what has gone is gone and
can no longer cause suffering.

54:18.821 --> 54:21.723
Don't take this badly.

54:21.725 --> 54:23.591
But tomorrow, I
won't remember you.

54:23.593 --> 54:25.826
Ah.

54:25.828 --> 54:29.730
I only remember
things from long ago.

54:29.732 --> 54:32.332
Perhaps it's not even
the first time we've met.

54:32.334 --> 54:33.167
No, no.

54:33.169 --> 54:34.134
It is.

54:34.136 --> 54:35.669
I would have told you otherwise.

54:35.671 --> 54:41.709
Ah, but you see, I would
have already forgotten.

54:41.711 --> 54:42.645
Please, the chair.

54:46.616 --> 54:48.315
Do you remember your husband?

54:48.317 --> 54:53.322
Not really, just a vague
idea of his existence.

54:53.324 --> 54:58.527
But I couldn't put a
face to any feeling.

54:58.529 --> 54:59.594
I understand.

54:59.596 --> 55:02.664
Is he doing OK?

55:02.666 --> 55:06.101
Well, actually, that's
hard to say right now.

55:06.103 --> 55:09.605
Whether he's alive or dead,
it makes no difference to me.

55:09.607 --> 55:13.809
Unfortunately, he's
just a stranger.

55:13.811 --> 55:16.679
Was I happy when I was with him?

55:16.681 --> 55:20.782
Honestly, I don't know.

55:20.784 --> 55:24.920
I just came to give
you his watch back.

55:24.922 --> 55:29.523
If you leave it here,
I'll forget it when you go.

55:29.525 --> 55:32.193
If you give it to me, I'll
be asking myself where

55:32.195 --> 55:33.365
it came from by this evening.

55:38.370 --> 55:44.040
If you keep it, at least
one person will think of it.

55:44.042 --> 55:45.508
I thank you for your time.

55:45.510 --> 55:47.711
I won't bother you much longer.

55:47.713 --> 55:50.946
And I'll make sure your son,
Charlie, gets the watch.

55:50.948 --> 55:55.785
I may have lost my memory,
but I still know I bore a child.

55:55.787 --> 55:58.220
And whatever else
it might have been,

55:58.222 --> 56:00.425
it most certainly was not a boy.

57:00.618 --> 57:01.119
TRAINER: Control.

57:10.530 --> 57:11.030
Again.

57:14.168 --> 57:14.668
Breathe.

57:51.872 --> 57:52.773
No breath.

58:17.899 --> 58:18.400
Balance.

58:22.670 --> 58:23.171
Silence.

58:45.126 --> 58:45.628
Control.

59:10.686 --> 59:12.588
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

59:31.173 --> 59:32.776
Now I know why you're here.

59:43.453 --> 59:44.986
BOB [ON PHONE]:
Jerry, this is Bob.

59:44.988 --> 59:46.520
Now you will receive
all the [INAUDIBLE]

59:46.522 --> 59:48.087
communications on your phone.

59:48.089 --> 59:48.991
KAPPA: Thanks, Bob.

01:00:01.538 --> 01:00:04.438
I'm going to do it tomorrow.

01:00:04.440 --> 01:00:07.678
Yeah, you've been
saying that for days now.

01:00:10.745 --> 01:00:12.148
[PHONE CHIMING]

01:00:14.384 --> 01:00:15.783
Captain.

01:00:15.785 --> 01:00:17.118
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
Are you sitting down?

01:00:17.120 --> 01:00:18.886
Yeah, come on.
What is it?

01:00:18.888 --> 01:00:21.523
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: She
arrived in the US a month ago.

01:00:21.525 --> 01:00:22.657
You're sure?

01:00:22.659 --> 01:00:23.624
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: The
same passport number,

01:00:23.626 --> 01:00:25.494
the same airline as the funeral.

01:00:25.496 --> 01:00:26.994
However, not a
trace of credit card

01:00:26.996 --> 01:00:29.296
use... no Visa or Amex, zilch.

01:00:29.298 --> 01:00:31.266
She must be paying
everything in cash.

01:00:31.268 --> 01:00:32.967
We can't get any lead on her.

01:00:32.969 --> 01:00:35.304
Well, when's the
return schedule for?

01:00:35.306 --> 01:00:37.505
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
There's no return planned.

01:00:37.507 --> 01:00:39.307
That means she's found him.

01:00:39.309 --> 01:00:40.474
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
How could anyone

01:00:40.476 --> 01:00:42.711
track down a killer like him?

01:00:42.713 --> 01:00:45.680
When what's needed to be
done to find him is done.

01:00:45.682 --> 01:00:46.814
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
I don't get it.

01:00:46.816 --> 01:00:49.050
Look, he's deliberately
leaving a trail.

01:00:49.052 --> 01:00:50.218
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: They?

01:00:50.220 --> 01:00:51.385
Is he that stupid?

01:00:51.387 --> 01:00:52.019
No.

01:00:52.021 --> 01:00:53.255
I don't think so.

01:00:53.257 --> 01:00:56.224
Look, when you want someone
to retrace your steps,

01:00:56.226 --> 01:00:57.825
you sign-post it, right?

01:00:57.827 --> 01:00:59.695
And that's exactly
what he's done.

01:00:59.697 --> 01:01:00.829
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: They?

01:01:00.831 --> 01:01:01.762
What?

01:01:01.764 --> 01:01:02.731
Why?

01:01:02.733 --> 01:01:04.365
Because he's
expecting other, OK?

01:01:04.367 --> 01:01:07.735
But only just like us, he's
expecting to find a son.

01:01:07.737 --> 01:01:09.605
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
Excuse me, Kappa.

01:01:09.607 --> 01:01:11.207
- But I'm still a bit lost here.
- No.

01:01:11.209 --> 01:01:12.475
Listen to me.

01:01:12.477 --> 01:01:17.413
He's waiting for his prey
to make the first move.

01:01:17.415 --> 01:01:19.283
[PANTING]

01:01:35.133 --> 01:01:37.736
HENRY: I thought you would
hesitate at least for a second.

01:01:44.843 --> 01:01:47.542
The weight will be
so intensely crushing

01:01:47.544 --> 01:01:50.014
that, eventually, you'll
find the strength to move.

01:01:52.950 --> 01:01:55.585
We don't really know
our own bodies till we

01:01:55.587 --> 01:01:56.623
push them to the limits.

01:01:59.224 --> 01:02:02.094
Right now, you're just making
acquaintance with yours.

01:02:05.398 --> 01:02:07.398
So you're a torture expert.

01:02:07.400 --> 01:02:09.802
That's an insult after
the way I've nursed you.

01:02:16.641 --> 01:02:17.309
Who are you?

01:02:21.047 --> 01:02:23.981
If your legs are
squashed for too long,

01:02:23.983 --> 01:02:26.753
your veins will
become irreparable.

01:02:35.594 --> 01:02:37.360
If you stay like that
for another minute,

01:02:37.362 --> 01:02:39.463
you limp for the
rest of your life.

01:02:39.465 --> 01:02:41.934
After 10, you won't walk again.

01:02:44.937 --> 01:02:48.508
I'll say it again.
Who are you?

01:03:00.285 --> 01:03:03.187
I know who you are.

01:03:03.189 --> 01:03:06.758
I know what you do for a living.

01:03:06.760 --> 01:03:08.562
And I came here to kill you.

01:03:13.966 --> 01:03:16.399
Oh.

01:03:16.401 --> 01:03:18.136
When I take off the
log, the pain will

01:03:18.138 --> 01:03:20.470
be more acute than it is now.

01:03:20.472 --> 01:03:21.675
After, you'll feel better.

01:03:30.716 --> 01:03:32.216
Ah, ah, ah!

01:03:32.218 --> 01:03:33.217
Ah!

01:03:33.219 --> 01:03:36.387
[MOANS] Fuck!

01:03:36.389 --> 01:03:40.224
There you go.

01:03:40.226 --> 01:03:41.527
Are you leaving?

01:03:41.529 --> 01:03:43.161
Yep.

01:03:43.163 --> 01:03:45.197
The storm is too strong.

01:03:45.199 --> 01:03:47.835
- Even wolves don't come out.
- Great.

01:03:50.603 --> 01:03:53.773
[CHUCKLES] That's funny.

01:03:53.775 --> 01:03:56.507
I saw her about a
week ago, maybe more.

01:03:56.509 --> 01:03:58.143
She's fearless.

01:03:58.145 --> 01:03:59.411
Yeah?

01:03:59.413 --> 01:04:00.512
Nah.

01:04:00.514 --> 01:04:01.380
An hour away from here.

01:04:01.382 --> 01:04:02.980
She was going east.

01:04:02.982 --> 01:04:04.550
But if I were you,
I'd wait a bit.

01:04:04.552 --> 01:04:05.353
It'll blow hard.

01:04:15.931 --> 01:04:19.398
And unfortunately, we
don't have French toast.

01:04:19.400 --> 01:04:20.803
[TEXT MESSAGE BLEEP]

01:04:41.390 --> 01:04:44.024
I don't remember his face.

01:04:44.026 --> 01:04:46.492
He knew yours by heart.

01:04:46.494 --> 01:04:48.363
MELODY: You were not
paid to know that.

01:04:51.966 --> 01:04:56.035
The absence of parents can
cause emotional immaturity.

01:04:56.037 --> 01:05:01.177
I will classify this as a
provocation in this category.

01:05:04.113 --> 01:05:08.516
I spent every Christmas
with you, but not with him.

01:05:08.518 --> 01:05:12.453
It's your father
who bought your gifts.

01:05:12.455 --> 01:05:15.590
That's not true, Brigleur.

01:05:15.592 --> 01:05:17.692
When I was 14, I
followed you into a store

01:05:17.694 --> 01:05:20.393
when you bought me the flute.

01:05:20.395 --> 01:05:24.165
BRIGLEUR: And you broke it
the minute you unpacked it.

01:05:24.167 --> 01:05:26.165
Yeah.

01:05:26.167 --> 01:05:27.701
I thought I'd get a
slap or something,

01:05:27.703 --> 01:05:30.570
but you didn't even move.

01:05:30.572 --> 01:05:32.408
That's why I knew you'd never
be anything but an employee.

01:05:38.348 --> 01:05:39.647
MELODY [VOICEOVER]:
He missed my birth.

01:05:39.649 --> 01:05:42.782
I missed his death.

01:05:42.784 --> 01:05:44.518
I did everything to be like him.

01:05:44.520 --> 01:05:46.252
I dressed like him.

01:05:46.254 --> 01:05:48.057
I studied what he studied.

01:05:50.993 --> 01:05:52.458
I wrote him a
letter every week so

01:05:52.460 --> 01:05:56.166
that he would know everything
about me, like a real father.

01:05:58.769 --> 01:06:03.004
Every Saturday, I'd run and
hide at the boarding school

01:06:03.006 --> 01:06:04.775
so that I could see him
arrive to pick me up.

01:06:07.778 --> 01:06:09.477
And then when he dropped
me off, I'd run and hide

01:06:09.479 --> 01:06:10.814
so I could see him leave.

01:06:17.186 --> 01:06:19.589
If you only knew the things I
do behind your back, Brigleur.

01:06:24.861 --> 01:06:28.863
BRIGLEUR: Malcolm is much
less naive than I am.

01:06:28.865 --> 01:06:32.867
You're going to have to become
accustomed to his presence.

01:06:32.869 --> 01:06:36.006
It's stipulated in the
insurance contract.

01:06:48.286 --> 01:06:52.621
[SIGHS] I liked it
better when we were kids.

01:06:52.623 --> 01:06:53.524
Me too.

01:06:57.094 --> 01:06:59.964
[WIND HOWLING]

01:07:27.926 --> 01:07:32.729
The Ski-Doo's not
working anymore.

01:07:32.731 --> 01:07:35.499
If you want to go away,
the path is clear.

01:07:35.501 --> 01:07:37.467
You don't have the
balls to kill me.

01:07:37.469 --> 01:07:39.304
And you're going to
let nature do it?

01:08:02.695 --> 01:08:05.832
You killed my father, and
now you're toying with me.

01:08:10.302 --> 01:08:11.403
Tell me why I'm still alive.

01:08:21.913 --> 01:08:23.782
The art of war is...

01:08:23.783 --> 01:08:25.916
Oh, for fuck's sake.

01:08:25.917 --> 01:08:29.687
I'm going to die here,
and you're fucking quoting

01:08:29.689 --> 01:08:31.790
your stupid fucking book.

01:08:31.792 --> 01:08:33.425
Fuck off with that shit.

01:08:33.426 --> 01:08:37.060
I need to understand.

01:08:37.062 --> 01:08:38.265
When did you figure it all out?

01:08:41.000 --> 01:08:46.104
The weight of your empty bag.

01:08:46.106 --> 01:08:47.337
Fuck.

01:08:47.339 --> 01:08:52.644
HENRY: The overly sharp
swerve of your handlebar.

01:08:52.645 --> 01:08:55.749
Falling asleep driving makes
you veer off gradually.

01:08:59.586 --> 01:09:03.323
No cell phone, no ID.

01:09:09.363 --> 01:09:11.232
Doubting is my nature.

01:09:19.272 --> 01:09:23.810
Did you look at him
before you killed him?

01:09:27.281 --> 01:09:29.184
Did you look at his face?

01:09:36.357 --> 01:09:38.193
Did he say anything,
like a name?

01:09:41.361 --> 01:09:45.466
Avenging your father
doesn't make you his daughter.

01:09:54.207 --> 01:09:56.775
He didn't even want a girl.

01:09:56.777 --> 01:09:58.246
That's why he called me Charlie.

01:10:01.683 --> 01:10:03.018
[SIGHS]

01:10:06.956 --> 01:10:07.890
So you're going to kill me.

01:10:12.527 --> 01:10:14.262
You're the second
part of the contract.

01:10:18.399 --> 01:10:20.400
[SIGHS]

01:10:20.402 --> 01:10:22.802
You don't think that it
was fully your decision

01:10:22.804 --> 01:10:23.972
to come here, do you?

01:10:31.612 --> 01:10:34.347
Who wants me dead?

01:10:34.349 --> 01:10:36.348
Give me a name.

01:10:36.350 --> 01:10:38.584
There is no name,
just a phone number.

01:10:38.586 --> 01:10:39.088
Give it to me.

01:10:45.161 --> 01:10:46.660
I'll take outside.

01:10:46.662 --> 01:10:48.565
[WIND ROARING]

01:11:11.487 --> 01:11:12.419
You've got to be kidding me.

01:11:12.421 --> 01:11:15.524
Come on.
Fuck.

01:11:21.564 --> 01:11:23.433
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:11:24.900 --> 01:11:25.402
Shit.

01:11:35.879 --> 01:11:37.748
[LIGHTS ZAP]
Fuck!

01:11:44.020 --> 01:11:44.521
Shit.

01:11:47.557 --> 01:11:48.924
Hey, Davies, listen.
It's me.

01:11:48.926 --> 01:11:52.359
The power's out, and I need
an internet connection.

01:11:52.361 --> 01:11:53.428
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: At 2 o'clock?

01:11:53.430 --> 01:11:54.463
Yeah, at 2:00 in the morning.

01:11:54.465 --> 01:11:55.531
Come on.

01:11:55.533 --> 01:11:56.700
DAVIES [ON PHONE]:
I'll go to my computer.

01:12:02.004 --> 01:12:02.970
KAPPA [ON PHONE]: OK, listen.

01:12:02.972 --> 01:12:04.206
I think I found it.

01:12:04.208 --> 01:12:06.073
Obviously, there's no credit
card transaction history

01:12:06.075 --> 01:12:07.675
because she doesn't have one.

01:12:07.677 --> 01:12:09.444
- What?
- Yeah.

01:12:09.446 --> 01:12:12.947
Brigleur organizes it,
takes care of all of it.

01:12:12.949 --> 01:12:14.182
It's Brigleur who pays.

01:12:14.184 --> 01:12:16.183
So if we find Brigleur's
account details,

01:12:16.185 --> 01:12:17.952
then we'll find signs
of the daughter.

01:12:17.954 --> 01:12:19.088
Right now?

01:12:19.090 --> 01:12:20.890
KAPPA [ON PHONE]:
Please, do it for me, OK?

01:12:20.892 --> 01:12:23.626
[SIGHS] All right.

01:12:23.628 --> 01:12:24.627
[BANGING]

01:12:24.629 --> 01:12:25.496
[ZAPPING]

01:12:27.566 --> 01:12:29.435
Oh, you're kidding me.

01:12:35.440 --> 01:12:37.308
[PHONE RINGING]

01:12:47.252 --> 01:12:48.219
Wait a second.

01:12:52.523 --> 01:12:58.059
Lieutenant, to what do I
owe this nocturnal pleasure?

01:12:58.061 --> 01:12:59.561
Where is she?

01:12:59.563 --> 01:13:00.729
BRIGLEUR [ON PHONE]:
You understand

01:13:00.731 --> 01:13:02.098
that I cannot answer you.

01:13:02.100 --> 01:13:03.033
I don't give a shit.

01:13:03.035 --> 01:13:04.367
Tell me where she is.

01:13:04.369 --> 01:13:05.835
BRIGLEUR [ON PHONE]: I
don't have the right.

01:13:05.837 --> 01:13:07.269
Well, who's going to
stop you, your boss?

01:13:07.271 --> 01:13:08.605
He's dead.

01:13:08.607 --> 01:13:10.507
BRIGLEUR [ON PHONE]: I am
paid to respect my contracts.

01:13:10.509 --> 01:13:11.941
I don't have the right to say.

01:13:11.943 --> 01:13:13.043
Listen to me.

01:13:13.045 --> 01:13:14.377
She's going to be dead
in a couple of hours

01:13:14.379 --> 01:13:16.145
if she's not dead already.
You understand?

01:13:16.147 --> 01:13:18.248
No matter what her training is,
it doesn't make a difference.

01:13:18.250 --> 01:13:20.685
This guy is more
than a professional.

01:13:20.687 --> 01:13:25.387
Do you have any
other questions?

01:13:25.389 --> 01:13:27.391
No.

01:13:27.393 --> 01:13:28.928
BRIGLEUR [ON PHONE]: Then
good night, Mr. Kappa.

01:13:41.205 --> 01:13:42.205
[PHONE CHIMING]

01:13:42.207 --> 01:13:43.039
Hey.

01:13:43.041 --> 01:13:44.374
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: I've got it.

01:13:44.376 --> 01:13:46.776
He paid for the ticket to
Washington state a month ago.

01:13:46.778 --> 01:13:47.977
KAPPA [ON PHONE]: Yep.

01:13:47.979 --> 01:13:49.747
When I talked to him, he
said he stayed in Europe.

01:13:49.749 --> 01:13:51.748
What about the second
number on Bob's list?

01:13:51.750 --> 01:13:53.550
KAPPA [ON PHONE]: Well,
he didn't pick up.

01:13:53.552 --> 01:13:55.452
Do you think it's
Charlie's number?

01:13:55.454 --> 01:13:56.654
No.

01:13:56.656 --> 01:14:00.792
He, she, whatever, I mean,
they would've picked up.

01:14:00.794 --> 01:14:02.696
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:14:04.296 --> 01:14:06.199
[WIND HOWLING]

01:14:22.782 --> 01:14:24.184
[PHONE DINGS]

01:14:26.787 --> 01:14:28.518
40 miles north of Oroville.

01:14:28.520 --> 01:14:32.456
Oroville, where the
hell is Oroville?

01:14:32.458 --> 01:14:36.861
Oroville, Oroville,
motherfucker.

01:14:36.863 --> 01:14:37.797
Bob, you're a genius.

01:14:40.433 --> 01:14:41.967
You asked for the
weather report...

01:14:41.969 --> 01:14:43.370
like I said.

01:15:15.903 --> 01:15:17.068
Captain, listen.

01:15:17.070 --> 01:15:19.037
Call me when you
get to Oroville, OK?

01:15:19.039 --> 01:15:20.339
I've got the exact location.

01:15:20.341 --> 01:15:21.540
Meet me there.

01:15:21.542 --> 01:15:22.741
DAVIES [ON PHONE]: Kappa,
we've got no warrant.

01:15:22.743 --> 01:15:23.808
No, listen.

01:15:23.810 --> 01:15:25.177
We're not going to
go and arrest anyone.

01:15:25.179 --> 01:15:27.148
We're going to go and save her
before he does anything, OK?

01:15:50.138 --> 01:15:52.040
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:16:10.092 --> 01:16:13.993
CHARLIE: Sometimes I
forget that you killed him,

01:16:13.995 --> 01:16:15.397
and I hate myself for that.

01:16:19.066 --> 01:16:21.301
I need to remember
why I came here.

01:16:21.303 --> 01:16:22.172
[GUN SHOT]

01:16:30.781 --> 01:16:31.281
Charlie!

01:16:34.584 --> 01:16:35.085
Charlie!

01:16:48.665 --> 01:16:50.567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

01:17:18.094 --> 01:17:19.996
Aw, no, no.

01:17:31.774 --> 01:17:32.977
[SNOWBALL THUDDING]

01:17:53.029 --> 01:17:54.432
[PANTING]

01:18:21.460 --> 01:18:22.360
[WHIMPERS]

01:18:30.969 --> 01:18:33.337
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:19:23.855 --> 01:19:26.258
What's the price
for a girl like me?

01:19:31.831 --> 01:19:33.234
[GRUNTS]

01:19:58.691 --> 01:20:00.694
Malcolm's?
What do you think?

01:20:04.763 --> 01:20:06.165
[SNOWMOBILE REVVING]

01:20:21.147 --> 01:20:23.150
Oh!
Ah, ah, ah!

01:20:26.620 --> 01:20:27.122
Ah!

01:21:24.613 --> 01:21:27.016
Did you find what
you were looking for?

01:21:29.917 --> 01:21:36.522
You need to know that if
I hesitated even slightly,

01:21:36.524 --> 01:21:38.294
this would have been impossible.

01:21:41.196 --> 01:21:41.997
Close your eyes.

01:21:47.870 --> 01:21:48.770
[GROWLS]

01:21:54.342 --> 01:21:57.247
They never forget the
taste of blood, like me.

01:22:07.422 --> 01:22:08.621
Uh!

01:22:08.623 --> 01:22:09.126
Oh!

01:22:21.538 --> 01:22:32.416
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

01:22:51.835 --> 01:22:53.335
You good?

01:22:53.337 --> 01:22:54.836
Yeah, I'm good.

01:22:54.838 --> 01:22:55.339
That's enough.

